a3ComSysIpInterfaceIpStackIndex.name: a3ComSysIpInterfaceIpStackIndex
a3ComSysIpInterfaceIpStackIndex.description: The index of the IP stack identified by this entry relative to this agent.

a3ComSysIpInterfaceAddr.name: a3ComSysIpInterfaceAddr
a3ComSysIpInterfaceAddr.description: The IP address of this entry within the IP stack identified within this entry.

a3ComSysIpInterfaceNetMask.name: a3ComSysIpInterfaceNetMask
a3ComSysIpInterfaceNetMask.description: The subnet mask associated with this IP interface. The value of the mask is an IP address with all the network bits set to 1 and all the host bits set to 0.

a3ComSysIpInterfaceIndex.name: a3ComSysIpInterfaceIndex
a3ComSysIpInterfaceIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable. lspIPInterfaceIndex maps to the same interface as identified by ifIndex in the ifTable. Currently, this object can not be modified after creation.

a3ComSysIpInterfaceBcastAddr.name: a3ComSysIpInterfaceBcastAddr
a3ComSysIpInterfaceBcastAddr.description: This object represents the value of the least significant bit of this entry's direct broadcast address. For example, a value of one signifies that the host portion of the broadcast address is set to all ones.

a3ComSysIpInterfaceCost.name: a3ComSysIpInterfaceCost
a3ComSysIpInterfaceCost.description: The route cost metric used for this entry.

a3ComSysIpInterfaceStatus.name: a3ComSysIpInterfaceStatus
a3ComSysIpInterfaceStatus.description: The status column for this IP interface. This object can be set to: createAndGo(4) destroy(6) The following value may be read: active(1) Setting this object to createAndGo(4) causes the agent to attempt to create and commit the row based on the contents of the object in the row. If all necessary information is present in the row and the values are acceptable to the agent, the agent will change the status to active(1). If any of the necessary objects are not available the agent will reject the request. Other objects in this row entry can be individually modified while the row status is active(1). Setting this object to destroy(6) will remove this entry.

a3ComSysIpxInterfaceCount.name: a3ComSysIpxInterfaceCount
a3ComSysIpxInterfaceCount.description: A count of the total number of IPX interfaces configured.

a3ComSysIpxInterfaceTable.name: a3ComSysIpxInterfaceTable
a3ComSysIpxInterfaceTable.description: A list of configured IPX interfaces.

a3ComSysIpxInterfaceIpxStackIndex.name: a3ComSysIpxInterfaceIpxStackIndex
a3ComSysIpxInterfaceIpxStackIndex.description: The index of the IPX stack identified by this entry relative to this agent.

a3ComSysIpxInterfaceNetNumber.name: a3ComSysIpxInterfaceNetNumber
a3ComSysIpxInterfaceNetNumber.description: The IPX Network Number of this entry.

a3ComSysIpxInterfaceIfIndex.name: a3ComSysIpxInterfaceIfIndex
a3ComSysIpxInterfaceIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the virtual interface that this IPX interface is is configured over. The a3ComSysIpxInterfaceIfIndex identifies a virtual interface, for example a VLAN, that this local address is associated with for purposes of routing or network management.

a3ComSysIpxInterfaceCost.name: a3ComSysIpxInterfaceCost
a3ComSysIpxInterfaceCost.description: The cost associated with the IPX address of this entry.

a3ComSysIpxInterfaceFrameType.name: a3ComSysIpxInterfaceFrameType
a3ComSysIpxInterfaceFrameType.description: The frame format used for routing frames on this IPX interface. The framing formats are for ethernet ports. There are two frame formats for FDDI ports: 802.2 and FDDI SNAP. The correct FDDI format is automatically chosen if this interface is associated with a VLAN interface that contains both ethernet and FDDI ports. If the VLAN interface is an FDDI port, than the only values that can be written to this object are: frame-802-2(2) and frame-SNAP(4).

a3ComSysIpxInterfaceStatus.name: a3ComSysIpxInterfaceStatus
a3ComSysIpxInterfaceStatus.description: The status column for this IPX interface. This OBJECT can be set to: createAndGo(4) destroy(6) The following value may be read: active(1) Setting this object ot createAndGo(4) causes the agent to attempt to create and commit the row based on the contents of the object in the row. If all necessary information is present in the row and the values are acceptable to the agent, the agent will change the status to active(1). If any of the necessary objects are not available the agent will reject the request. Other objects in this row entry can be individually modified while the row status is active(1). Setting this object to destroy(6) will remove this entry.

a3ComSysAtInterfaceCount.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceCount
a3ComSysAtInterfaceCount.description: A count of the total number of AppleTalk interfaces configured.

a3ComSysAtInterfaceTable.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceTable
a3ComSysAtInterfaceTable.description: A list of AppleTalk ports for this entity.

a3ComSysAtInterfaceEntry.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceEntry
a3ComSysAtInterfaceEntry.description: An individual appletalk interface entry. Appletalk entries with row status of active(1) cannot be modified but must set to destroy(6) and recreated.

a3ComSysAtInterfaceAtStackIndex.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceAtStackIndex
a3ComSysAtInterfaceAtStackIndex.description: The index of the Appletalk stack identified by this entry relative to this agent. Setting of this object is required for all interface creations.

a3ComSysAtInterfaceNetAddress.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceNetAddress
a3ComSysAtInterfaceNetAddress.description: The AppleTalk network address configured for this port.

a3ComSysAtInterfaceType.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceType
a3ComSysAtInterfaceType.description: The type of interface that is configured for this port. Setting of this object is required for all interface creations.

a3ComSysAtInterfaceNetStart.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceNetStart
a3ComSysAtInterfaceNetStart.description: The first AppleTalk network address in the range configured for this port. If this port is not a native AppleTalk port, this object shall have the value of two octets of zero. Setting of this object is mandatory only for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceNetEnd.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceNetEnd
a3ComSysAtInterfaceNetEnd.description: The last AppleTalk network address in the range configured for this port. If the network to which this AppleTalk port is connected is a non-extended network, or if it is not a native AppleTalk port, the value for a3ComSysAtInterfaceNetEnd shall be two octets of zero. Setting of this object is mandatory only for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZoneDefault.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZoneDefault
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZoneDefault.description: The name of the default zone for this port. If this port only has one zone, that zone is represented here. Setting of this object is mandatory for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone1.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone1
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone1.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone2.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone2
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone2.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone3.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone3
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone3.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone4.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone4
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone4.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone5.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone5
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone5.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone6.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone6
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone6.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone7.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone7
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone7.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone8.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone8
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone8.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone9.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone9
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone9.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone10.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone10
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone10.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone11.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone11
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone11.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone12.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone12
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone12.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone13.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone13
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone13.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone14.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone14
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone14.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone15.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone15
a3ComSysAtInterfaceZone15.description: Zone name in this entry's zone list. This object may only only be set for interfaces with a3ComSysAtInterfaceType equal to seedInterface(1).

a3ComSysAtInterfaceIfIndex.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceIfIndex
a3ComSysAtInterfaceIfIndex.description: The interface associated with this AppleTalk port. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex in the ifTable. Setting of this object is required for all interface creations.

a3ComSysAtInterfaceState.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceState
a3ComSysAtInterfaceState.description: The current state of the appletalk interface.

a3ComSysAtInterfaceStatus.name: a3ComSysAtInterfaceStatus
a3ComSysAtInterfaceStatus.description: The status column for this IP interface. This object can be set to: createAndGo(4) createAndWait(5) destroy(6) The following value may be read: active(1) notInService(2) Setting this object to createAndGo(4) causes the agent to attempt to create and commit the row based on the contents of the object in the row. If all necessary information is present in the row and the values are acceptable to the agent, the agent will change the status to active(1). If any of the necessary objects are not available the agent will reject the request. Setting this object to createAndWait(5) causes the agent to create an entry which has the value notInService(2). Only three notInService(2) entries are permitted at any one time.
